{"title":"Deficiencia del inhibidor C1","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/Deficiencia del inhibidor C1-2024-1.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Deficiencia del\\NInhibidor C1","guid":"tDVJyJAIPiePb6Djk7HbSw","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Perlas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"¿Cuál es el mediador primario de\\Ninflamación en HAE? R: Bradicinina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"¿Cuál es la herencia de HAE tipos I y\\NII? R: Autosómica dominante","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"¿Niveles de qué complemento\\Nestán disminuidos en 95% de\\Nlos casos? R: C4","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"¿Cuál es la prioridad en el tratamiento de\\Nun ataque agudo? R: Mantener\\Npermeabilidad de vías aéreas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"¿Qué niveles de complemento distinguen HAE de\\Ndeficiencia adquirida de C1-INH? R: C1q normal en\\NHAE, bajo en deficiencia adquirida","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"0","text":"Definición:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"Condición hereditaria o adquirida caracterizada por\\Nbajos niveles funcionales del inhibidor C1, causando\\Nangioedema recurrente sin urticaria.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"9","parent":"0","text":"Fisiología del\\NComplemento:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"10","parent":"9","text":"Sistema de defensa inmune innato,\\Ncompuesto por proteínas\\Nplasmáticas y de membrana.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"9","text":"Tres vías de activación:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"Clásica: mediada por\\Ncomplejos antígeno-anticuerpo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"11","text":"Alternativa: por\\Nsuperficies microbianas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"11","text":"Lectina: por\\Nresiduos de\\Nmanosa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"15